PROFILE ACTIONS.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

There are various profile actions that allow you to manage your
profiles. These are accessed from the Profiles menu.  Highlight the
profile that you want to act on by a single click and choose the
appropriate action and profile type from the available drop-down
menu.

DELETE PROFILE.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This deletes the highlighted profile of the type chosen from the menu.
You will be warned if the profile is attached to any diagnostics in the list.
If you continue, it will delete any references to the profile in the list.

COPY PROFILE.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This copies the highlighted profile of the type chosen from the menu.
Choose a new name.
You can then redefine the profile using the EDIT PROFILE option. This allows
you to create a new profile similar to another on with the minimum effort.

EDIT PROFILE.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This takes you into the highlighted profile of the type chosen from the menu.
You can change the attributes of the profile, including the NAME.
You should always VERIFY after doing this to avoid problems with diagnostics
being attached to profiles that have been renamed. This will also check that
the profile definition does not clash with any diagnostics to which it is
attached.

If you change the name, this name change will also apply where the
profile has been attached to the diagnostics list. NOTE if you change
a name but then "Abandon" STASH, the name in the diagnostics table
will revert to the original, but the name of the profile won't. So
always use Close after doing this.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

ATTACHING PROFILES.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Attach profiles with the mouse or the space key. Click on the
profile(s) that you want to attach and then double click on the
diagnostic that you want to attach them to.  Double click on the
diagnostic name to attach all three profiles.  Double click on the
relevant profile column to attach just one profile.

